p2
VSiblings on a song
p3
sVnews
p4
VHe came, crooned and made the youngsters among the railway employees of Vijayawada division dance in frenzy to foot-tapping songs. Popular playback singer Hema Chandra along with Hima Bindu enthralled the packed audience at Rail Stadium last weekend at Surabhi, a musical feast organised by the South Central Railway Women's Welfare Organisation (SCRWWO), Vijayawada Division, on the occasion of its annual day.Gayathri Jayanth, president of the organisation released a souvenir before the commencement of the programme and gave an inspiring speech on the plight of the girls in the society. Hema Chandra along with Hima Bindu belted out a couple of melodious songs, followed by the fast-paced numbers. He invited children on to the stage and along with them gyrated to the tunes in a splendid manner. Songs such as Bommali Bommali from Billa, Ringa Ringa... from Arya 2 and Aaj ki Raat from Don were well-received by the young audience.The senior citizens present in good number enjoyed the old melody Niluvave Vaalu Kanuladaana..., for which Senior Divisional Mechanical Engineer Pradeep went on stage to give an impromptu performance. SCR General Manager M.S. Jayanth, Vijayawada Division DRM Vashista Johri, SCRWWO Vijayawada unit president Seema Johri and others took part in the function.
